snippet.textDisplay:
Lenny is the happiest kid I’ve ever seen in my entire life.

Currently on vacation and I’m surrounded by many children .. I’ve rarely heard any of the kids laugh :/ kinda sad eh..

We lived in a basement and a family with young kids were living upstairs. All we heard was yelling .. the parents yelling and the kids whaling .. screaming.. once we left .. we never realized how much that affected us.. so much negativity.. I never heard those kids laugh..

I don’t experience kids much .. but it’s really been such an amazing treat to peer into your lives and watch your family. It’s great watching little Lenny experience things and laugh and growl! So cute! You guys are making me want to have a kid of my own haha

Seriously Awesome video!! Thanks for sharing

snippet.textDisplay: Omg this is where I grew up sailing. Portsmouth, RI in fact, you have to go to Bristol, RI the cutest little town you will ever visit. If you can go during 4th of July it is super special. They have the oldest 4th of July parade/celebration in the USA. Also there is a small pond/lazy river off of prudence island. I think it’s called nags pond or something like that if I remember correctly. It is the best, it is a tidal pond that had hundreds of crabs and you can go digging for clams. When I was a kid we would anchor the sailboat, snorkel and swim for hours and then have a big clam bowl on the beach with fresh clams that we found. It was amazing!!! I live in Utah now, but I do miss sailing in Narraganset bay a lot!!!! Loved this video!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Now that you are not tied up to the dock there anymore: Fun fact: In 1723, Goat Island (where Gurney's is) had 26 pirates buried on the shore between the high and low tide marks on the North end of the island. They were hanged at nearby Easton's Point. It was considered to be "the most extensive execution of pirates that ever took place at one time in the colonies." Just an interesting history fact :)


Once a Rhode Islander, always a Rhode Islander and you tend to know weird tidbits of knowledge. There is a lot of history in my little state despite being the smallest in the country :) Glad you guys got to spend time there and enjoy it! Newport is a fantastic place to be. Keep up the awesome video editing and making! You guys make the workday much less painful haha
